cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a new approach for training deep neural networks using ReLU activation function. The paper focuses on improving the network performance and reducing overfitting. The approach is evaluated on various tasks such as classification and detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new approach for training deep neural networks, it can also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
